Description:
    Installs FormDurationTracker for a model and controller with complete setup
    including migration, model concern, controller concern, and test files.

Example:
    rails generate form_duration_tracker:install Post started_at

    This will:
        - Create migration to add started_at column
        - Inject FormDurationTracker::ModelConcern into Post model
        - Inject FormDurationTracker::ControllerConcern into PostsController
        - Generate test files (RSpec or Minitest auto-detected)

Migration Options:
    --index              Add database index on the column
    --not-null           Add NOT NULL constraint
    --check-not-future   Add CHECK constraint to prevent future timestamps (PostgreSQL)

Model Options:
    --prevent-future            Prevent future timestamps validation
    --prevent-update            Prevent updating timestamp after creation
    --validate-max-duration     Maximum form duration (e.g., "2.hours")
    --validate-min-duration     Minimum form duration (e.g., "5.seconds")

Controller Options:
    --controller-name           Custom controller name (default: ModelNameController)
    --expirable                 Enable session expiration (default: true)
    --no-expirable              Disable session expiration
    --expiry-time               Session expiry time (default: "2.hours")
    --auto-initialize           Auto-initialize with before_action on :new
    --no-auto-initialize        Manual initialization (default)

Test Options:
    --test-framework            Test framework: rspec or minitest (auto-detected)

Skip Options:
    --skip-migration            Skip migration generation
    --skip-model                Skip model modification
    --skip-controller           Skip controller modification
    --skip-tests                Skip test file generation

Examples:

    # Basic installation
    rails g form_duration_tracker:install Post started_at

    # With database constraints
    rails g form_duration_tracker:install Post started_at \
      --index \
      --not-null \
      --check-not-future

    # With model validations
    rails g form_duration_tracker:install Post started_at \
      --prevent-future \
      --prevent-update \
      --validate-max-duration 2.hours \
      --validate-min-duration 5.seconds

    # With automatic controller initialization
    rails g form_duration_tracker:install Post started_at \
      --auto-initialize \
      --expiry-time 1.hour

    # Full featured
    rails g form_duration_tracker:install Post started_at \
      --index \
      --prevent-future \
      --prevent-update \
      --validate-max-duration 2.hours \
      --validate-min-duration 5.seconds \
      --auto-initialize \
      --expiry-time 2.hours

    # Custom controller name
    rails g form_duration_tracker:install Post started_at \
      --controller-name Admin::PostsController

    # Disable session expiration
    rails g form_duration_tracker:install Application form_started_at \
      --no-expirable \
      --auto-initialize

    # Skip controller modifications
    rails g form_duration_tracker:install Post started_at \
      --skip-controller \
      --prevent-future

    # Specify test framework
    rails g form_duration_tracker:install Post started_at \
      --test-framework rspec

    # Custom attribute name
    rails g form_duration_tracker:install Survey form_started_at \
      --index \
      --auto-initialize

Generated Files:
    - db/migrate/XXXXXX_add_started_at_to_posts.rb
    - Modified: app/models/post.rb
    - Modified: app/controllers/posts_controller.rb
    - spec/models/post_spec.rb (or test/models/post_test.rb)
    - spec/controllers/posts_controller_spec.rb (or test/controllers/posts_controller_test.rb)
